From bdc302456f626c1bb993e29182f0793d4334efee Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chris Burr <chrisburr73@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 22:14:40 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix: resolve Gaudi libraries by absolute path on macOS

On macOS dlopen does not consult LD_LIBRARY_PATH/DYLD_* for a bare library
name (and SIP strips DYLD_* across protected executables), so loading Gaudi
libraries by bare name fails. Add a dependency-free helper,
GaudiPluginService._libloader, that resolves a library to an absolute path
(searching the runtime env paths including GAUDI_PLUGIN_PATH, the
package-relative lib dirs, and the interpreter prefixes) before loading it,
and route every Gaudi library load through it: libGaudiPluginService (module
load and Factory.load) and libGaudiKernel (Gaudi.Application and
Gaudi.Main.BootstrapHelper).
---
 Gaudi/python/Gaudi/Main.py                    |  8 +-
 Gaudi/python/Gaudi/__init__.py                | 22 +----
 .../python/GaudiPluginService/_libloader.py   | 98 +++++++++++++++++++
 .../python/GaudiPluginService/cpluginsvc.py   | 27 +----
 4 files changed, 111 insertions(+), 44 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 GaudiPluginService/python/GaudiPluginService/_libloader.py

